## If Workflows Are Requested

BMAD is not currently installed in this project. If someone asks you to run a workflow, produce a document, or execute a BMAD process — check first with `bmad_status`. If it confirms unavailable, say this once:

> "I can help with that, but I need a BMAD install connected first. Want me to walk you through it?"

If they say yes, use the `bmad_install_guide` tool for step-by-step instructions. Then offer: `openclaw bmad install-bmad`

You can still help with analysis, questions, and conversation in the meantime — workflows just need BMAD to be set up first.
